<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - FUEL LEVEL GAUGE, SENDER, CIRCUITS
        AND CLUSTER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>FUEL LEVEL GAUGE, SENDER, CIRCUITS AND CLUSTER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_8.xml" xrefid="x0824507">Fuel Level Gauge
                    <xref refid="x0824507"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for operation description of fuel gauge system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fuel Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
            <para>This test will determine if the gauge is working. It does not determine if the gauge is reading
                accurately.
            </para>
            <table id="t0824505">
                <title>Fuel Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.26in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (127) circuit 36 at the fuel sender. Does gauge read above
                                    full scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(127), 36.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge reads above full scale.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect (127) and go to Fuel Gauge Circuit
                                    and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Use a test lead to jumper connector (127) circuit 36 to ground. Does gauge read at
                                    or below low scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(127), 36 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge reads at or below low scale.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit and cluster test good. Reconnect (127) and go to Fuel Gauge and Sender
                                    Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect (127) and go to Fuel Gauge Circuit
                                    and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fuel Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Fuel Gauge And Circuit Quick Test prior to performing this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824506">
                <title>Fuel Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (127) from fuel sender. Measure resistance to ground at
                                    circuit 36-G.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(127), 36-G to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 36-G/11-GU, then repair</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove connector (72) from the gauge cluster. At connector (72) measure resistance
                                    to ground at circuit 36A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(72), 36A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 36A, connector (102)/(338*) or circuit 36, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At fuel sender connector (127) use test lead to jumper circuit 36 to 36-G. At
                                    connector (72) measure resistance to ground at circuit 36A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 36A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 36A, connector (102) or (338*) with
                                    Detroit Diesel, or circuit 36, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove fuel gauge. Measure resistance between cluster connector (72) cavity 2 and
                                    the fuel gauge ground pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 2, to ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (72) cavity 4, and the fuel gauge
                                    sender pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 4, to sender pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (72) cavity 6, and the fuel gauge
                                    ignition pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 6, to ignition pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Reconnect (72) and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Turn key on. Measure voltage at fuel gauge ignition pin to ground, to check
                                    circuit 28A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28B/13D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure voltage between fuel gauge ignition and ground pins, to check circuit
                                    11-GW/11-GD.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Circuit checks good, Re-install gauge and go to Fuel Gauge and Sender Test.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GW/11-GD, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">* With Detroit Diesel 60 Series Engine</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fuel Gauge and Sender Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Test Fuel Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test prior to performing this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824507">
                <title>Fuel Gauge and Sender Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect gauge tester ZTSE-2781
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824516">(Figure 16)</hotlnk>
                                    and
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824517">(Figure 17)</hotlnk>
                                    to connector (127) circuit 36 and ground. Set to 1 ohm. Does fuel gauge read empty?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(127), 36 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With gauge tester still connected, set to 88 ohms. Does fuel gauge read full?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(127), 36 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>88 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge and circuits check good. Replace sender.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
